{"lemma":"طَمِّ","slug":"طَمِّ","root":"ط.م.م","root_slug":"ط-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27043","n27048","n27049"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27043","headword_ar":"طَمَّ","root":"Tm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [by rule it should be"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TumuwmN","text_ar":"طُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) said of water,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, abundant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rose high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a high pitch."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamaY","text_ar":"طَمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a","text_ar":"طَمَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a sayolu AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"طَمَّ سَيْلُ الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The torrent of the valley"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-course"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a high pitch, and predominated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY AlwaAdiY faTam~a EalaY AlqariY~i","text_ar":"جَرَى الوَادِى فَطَمَّ عَلَى القَرِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in explanation of which Meyd says, i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The torrent of the valley"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-course"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayolu AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"سَيْلُ الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in the Provs. of Meyd,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and filled up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choked up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed by filling up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choking up, the channel by which the water ran into the meadow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and he says that the prov. is applied to the case in which evil exceeds the ordinary limit: (Har p. 127:) [or, accord. to Z, it means a man's overcoming his adversary: (Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 278:) but it should be observed that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a","text_ar":"طَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense is trans. without a prep.:] one says of a torrent, (S, Meyd, and Har ubi suprà,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Alr~akiy~apa","text_ar":"طَمَّ الرَّكِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Meyd, K, Har,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) the latter on the authority of IAar, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It filled up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choked up, the well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafanahaA","text_ar":"دَفَنَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Meyd, K, Har,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabasahaA","text_ar":"كَبَسَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made it even"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saw~aAhaA","text_ar":"سَوَّاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the ground around it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Al$~aYo'a biAlt~uraAbi","text_ar":"طَمَّ الشَّىْءَ بِالتُّرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He covered over the thing with earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabasahu","text_ar":"كَبَسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a AlA_inaA='a","text_ar":"طَمَّ الاـِنَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled the vessel"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that the contents overflowed its edges:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Albiy^ora wagayorahaA biAlt~uraAbi","text_ar":"طَمَّ البِيْرَ وَغَيْرَهَا بِالتُّرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled the well &c. with earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust, so that it became even with the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~ahaA Alt~uraAbu","text_ar":"طَمَّهَا التُّرَابُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust, so filled it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"طَمَّ الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning as expl. in the beginning of the next preceding sentence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"طَمَّ الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TumuwmN","text_ar":"طُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing abounded so that it rose to a high pitch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had ascendency, and overcame."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a AlA^amoru","text_ar":"طَمَّ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, rose to a high pitch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had ascendency, and overcame:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formidable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 127.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN yTm~ wlA ytm~","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ يطمّ ولا يتمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaTim~u","text_ar":"يَطِمُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA yatim~u","text_ar":"وَلَا يَتِمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy, in order to assimilate the former verb with the latter, as is often done; meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair that is great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formidable, and that will not become accomplished"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~ati Alfitonapu","text_ar":"طَمَّتِ الفِتْنَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sedition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict and faction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhiyapN tTm~u EalaY","text_ar":"دَاهِيَةٌ تطمُّ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~awaAhY","text_ar":"الدَّوَاهى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTum~u","text_ar":"تَطُمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTim~u","text_ar":"تَطِمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calamity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that predominates over"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calamities"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 127.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Alfarasa","text_ar":"طَمَّ الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a EalayohaA","text_ar":"طَمَّ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the stallion)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaped the mare."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Al$~ajarapa","text_ar":"طَمَّ الشَّجَرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JM,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mounted upon the top of the tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a","text_ar":"طَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man and of a horse, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamiymN","text_ar":"طَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and quick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went away upon the face of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went away in any way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ran in an easy manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a","text_ar":"طَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamiymN","text_ar":"طَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ayaTim~u","text_ar":"مَرَّيَطِمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamiymN","text_ar":"طَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed along running in an easy manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and so, accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a","text_ar":"طَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TumuwmN","text_ar":"طُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamaY","text_ar":"طَمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a raA^osahu","text_ar":"طَمَّ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took somewhat from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hair of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his head;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gD~a minohu","text_ar":"غضَّ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K. [So in my MS. copy: in the CK and TA, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaD~a","text_ar":"عَضَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus in the TK, in which, however, the phrase is well expl., on the authority of the A, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he shaved a portion of his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also the pass. part. n.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a $aEarahu","text_ar":"طَمَّ شَعَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut his hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cut it off entirely."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a $aEarahu","text_ar":"طَمَّ شَعَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TumuwmN","text_ar":"طُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaSahu","text_ar":"عَقَصَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He plaited his hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twisted it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","K","TA","S","Meyd","Har","IAar","Msb","JM"]},{"entry_id":"n27048","headword_ar":"طَمٌّ","root":"Tm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.: see 1. ―         -b2-  As a subst.,] see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27049","headword_ar":"طِمٌّ","root":"Tm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) said to be so called because of its overwhelming what is in it ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^an~ahu","text_ar":"لِاَنَّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a EalaY maA fiyhi","text_ar":"طَمَّ عَلَى مَا فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): but in this sense the word is said to be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~N","text_ar":"طَمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and to be pronounced with kesr for the purpose of assimilating it to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rim~N","text_ar":"رِمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a biAlT~im~i waAlr~im~i","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ بِالطِّمِّ وَالرِّمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He brought much wealth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or the meaning in this instance is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAmr Alkvyr","text_ar":"الامر الكثير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amor Alkabiyr","text_ar":"الاَمْر الكَبِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which was a great event"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says As: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much of everything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much and little:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus accord. to Aboo-Tálib: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what was moist and what was dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves of trees, and what had fallen off from them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See more voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rim","text_ar":"رِم"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also what here follows.]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAm~N","text_ar":"طَامٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N TaAm~N","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ طَامٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rubbish and scum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, that is upon its surface;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is driven along by it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) and thus expl. as used in the saying above-mentioned. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large number:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and this also is said to be meant in the phrase above. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wonderful thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajabN","text_ar":"عَجَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajiybN","text_ar":"عَجِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which here, as in many other instances, evidently signify the same]: (K:) and this too is said to be meant in the phrase above. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male ostrich:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) because of the lightness of his pace. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A courser,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamiymN","text_ar":"طَمِيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, * TA: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TamuwmN","text_ar":"طَمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tim~N","text_ar":"طِمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of. his light and quick, or easy, running ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liTamiymi","text_ar":"لِطَمِيمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadowihi","text_ar":"عَدْوِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); or as being likened to the sea, as a horse is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHorN","text_ar":"بَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakobN","text_ar":"سَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garobN","text_ar":"غَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akar","text_ar":"ذَكَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) because its head is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTomuwm","text_ar":"مَطْمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though this epithet meant “ bare ”]. (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~im~u","text_ar":"الطِّمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said in the K to signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkay~isu","text_ar":"الكَيِّسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but [SM says] I think that this is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~am~u","text_ar":"الطَّمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkabosu","text_ar":"الكَبْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tam~a Alr~akiy~apa","text_ar":"طَمَّ الرَّكِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the first paragraph]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}